      "writtenOn": "2019-09-03T12:34:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Alerts are based on the keys and values of the data, right? (i.e. Params)  TraceIDs are a verbose way to encapsulate those keys/values, right?\n\nIf these Params are generate from a file, i.e. from a bot, then couldn\u0027t you send:\nstruct {\n  GroupParams Params\n  IndividualParams []Params\n}\n\nAssuming 20 group params (\u003c 300 bytes for key and value), 9k tests (each with 1k of params), you\u0027d be right at the 10 MB data limit for PubSub.\n\nIf all you care about are group params and \"name\", \"source_type\", \"bench_type\", then you could have up to 100k tests, without having to write to BT.",
